Document: class_skinreference
Path: godot/classes/class_skinreference.rst
Summary: An internal object mapping a Skin to a skeleton's RID in the RenderingServer for MeshInstance3D.

An internal object containing a mapping from a Skin used within the context of a particular MeshInstance3D to refer to the skeleton's RID in the RenderingServer. See MeshInstance3D.get_skin_reference() and RenderingServer.instance_attach_skeleton() for related methods.

Note: The skeleton RID used in the RenderingServer does not have a direct one-to-one correspondence to a Skeleton3D node. A Skeleton3D node with no MeshInstance3D children may be unknown to the RenderingServer. A Skeleton3D with multiple MeshInstance3D nodes using different skin objects may have multiple SkinReference instances and multiple skeleton RIDs.
---CHUNK---
Document: SkinReference
Path: godot/classes/class_skinreference.rst
Summary: Two read-only methods for retrieving skeleton and skin references in 3D mesh instances.

Methods:
- RID get_skeleton() 
  Returns the RID owned by this SkinReference, as returned by RenderingServer.skeleton_create()

- Skin get_skin() 
  Returns the Skin connected to this SkinReference. If a MeshInstance3D has no skin assigned, this references an internal default Skin owned by that MeshInstance3D. Note that a single Skin may have multiple SkinReferences if shared across Skeleton3D nodes.